title: 2018 FIFA World Cup qualifier: Indian Team trains ahead of Oman game
text:
2018 FIFA World Cup qualifier: Indian Team trains ahead of Oman game (Syed Fasiuddin/Muscat Daily) October 12, 2015 
The Indian football team, which arrived in Muscat in the early hours of Sunday, had its first training session at the Sultan Qaboos Sports Complex on Sunday evening. 
Coach Stephen Constantine led the boys at practice as they prepare to take on Oman in a joint qualifier for the 2018 FIFA World Cup and the 2019 AFC Asian Cup on Tuesday. 
The match begins at 6.30pm Similar content
